        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> I just read through the Play nice Policy:</P><P><a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/support/customer_service/cs_rules_of_conduct.jsp" target="_blank">http://eqlive.station.sony.com/support/customer_service/cs_rules_of_conduct.jsp</a></P><P>I was worried because a person on another thread said that you can be banned but I’m assuming that it takes multiple noticies before they do anything?</P><P>I only had one semi-bad experience. I was a ranger and the other person was a necro. In Oasis I was practicing my bow. I’d snare a croc and plink him with the bow until it broke, then I’d either re-snare or knife him, depending on how close. This was a while ago; only five colors for conned mobs.</P><P>There were a lot of peeps around but I know no one was on this croc, he was going straight up a valley between the dunes, towards the gypsies. I had watched him for a few seconds because he was outta snare range. He was at full health. I snared and plinked him four – six times when the nec came over a dune and hit it with a DoT. From the effect I guess it was heat blood. I didn’t say anything, just switched to Invoke Lightning, a few kicks and sword blows and the croc was dead.</P><P>The nec comes screaming up, “Hey you KS me!”, and starts shouting to the zone. I could understand him not seeing me plinking the croc. I calmly /tell him, “I had him rooted and was shooting him with my bow.” It was nice and rare for a woodie to look down to another player. He kept up with the KS speech to me and shouting to the zone, while I was calmly /telling him my point. I asked why the croc didn’t come after him when he nuked it. No answer. I was actually killing other things while he was yelling at me and the zone. He threatened to get a GM, and sent me one reply saying “You KS from me and won’t say your sorry.” I said, (this is my life motto) “I’m sorry you don’t know what you are talking about.” Then said “I’ll be right here when the GM comes.” and went right on killing.</P><P>No GM came.</P><P>I can hear people reading this saying: he could have feared the croc. That’s true but he never said that he did. The croc was full health and when I snared it turned right around towards me.</P><P>I love both my ranger and nec, wish I could play them together.</P><P>Renovo - Druzzil Ro<BR>11 dead years</P><P>But most important, the policy does NOT say once a group has a camp, they keep it. I've heard that so often in CB, Hey this is our camp, leave! when I'm just passing through.</P><P> </font></td>

