         Camps should be respected IMO. If someone has been camping the ac for 24 hours lets say than they should get it and you should sit and wait untill they do and leave. I was in Crushbone the other day just for kicks. Go up in the tower and there was a group. i go to a wall away from the group and sit. one of the members comes up to me and says "Can't you see it's camped? LEAVE". I replyed with "Can't you see i'm just sitting here and not doing anything?" He didn't say a thing and went back to his group. about 5 minuts or so later I stand up and cast spirit armor on one of thier group members. Another person from the group sends me a tell and says "DONT KS or I WILL REPORT U" Now atr this point I got pissed killed vereything that spawned in that room with the group trying to ks me about 5 cycls. than finally got a nice tell from another perons in the group apologizing for the rudness of the group.</P><P>Point is if you are nice and wait your turn and dont speak before you know whats going on things will be good. As far as rooting goes from what i understand it is still not your mob since you have not engaed it. Someone walking by has no way of knowing that you are standing far and hiting it with your bow. Evene if the mob doesn't go ruching towards the PC some people wouldn't think ti's rooted. They would just be overly excited and try to kill it asap. </P><P>If I complained how many times i was ks'ed by a druid in RM i would die.</P><P>Dont worry about it too much.</P><P>Give you another example. drood stole my mob in RM. Died. Sent me a tell asking me if i can get him a res. Although he did still my mob i still helped the guy out. It all depends on who you play the game.</P><P>---Avrorr De`Morte---<BR> --40th lvl DE Necro--<BR>    -House of D'Inex-<BR>     Ayon Ro Server<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
